What determines the base address of the block?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 4, 22, 53, 43, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'mwelling', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 664047670, 'comment_body': 'Yes, I did experiment with this earlier. It gave the following warning.
> Warning: Yosys has only limited support for tri-state logic at the moment. (../../components/gpmc_to_wishbone.v:95)

I have tested https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleWire/pull/3/commits/13ee421f42081dceb27b72b44e6ae46226f2e897 commit in hardware which includes Verilog implementation of the tristate buffer.

https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleWire/blob/13ee421f42081dceb27b72b44e6ae46226f2e897/components/gpmc_to_wishbone.v#L69-L96
please check once @mwelling ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 5, 16, 44, 8, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ombhilare999', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 664048441, 'comment_body': "Replaced the mem with a single register and also reduce address width to 1 in latest commit https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleWire/pull/3/commits/13ee421f42081dceb27b72b44e6ae46226f2e897 (tested in hardware)

the result of bit changes is significant in the timing result:
```
Info: Max frequency for clock 'clk$SB_IO_IN_$glb_clk': 197.78 MHz (PASS at 12.00 MHz)
Info: Clock 'gpmc_clk$SB_IO_IN_$glb_clk' has no interior paths

Info: Max delay <async>                            -> <async>                           : 8.45 ns
Info: Max delay <async>                            -> negedge gpmc_clk$SB_IO_IN_$glb_clk: 6.72 ns
Info: Max delay posedge clk$SB_IO_IN_$glb_clk      -> <async>                           : 4.86 ns
Info: Max delay negedge gpmc_clk$SB_IO_IN_$glb_clk -> posedge clk$SB_IO_IN_$glb_clk     : 3.91 ns
```", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 5, 16, 46, 15, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ombhilare999', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 664166459, 'comment_body': 'I am guessing that it is safer to use the ICE40 primitive given this warning.
Perhaps we can use an if/generate to use the primitive for the ICE40 and then else do standard Verilog tristate.

Check here for examples of conditional hardware based on the target:
https://github.com/no2fpga/no2usb/blob/1b96d8b2d900c8f4025b3910ea2b5664a8aa50d2/rtl/usb_phy.v#L41
https://github.com/ultraembedded/cores/blob/master/sdram/rtl/sdram.v#L686', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 6, 0, 33, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'mwelling', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 664421321, 'comment_body': 'https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleWire/blob/c3ea29cc87af142fc3690d13fea38355c66efd56/components/gpmc_to_wishbone.v#L83-L100

pr_title: GPMC modes added in bone-common in univ | BeagleWire overlays added
pr_body:
Earlier it was not possible to use `config-pin` utility with `GPMC` as there were no defined gpmc modes in pinux of bone common file, So I tried adding them after discussion with @lorforlinux. I got everything worked now.

1) For all the pins I had added `gpmc_pin` mode here first:
  https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleBoard-DeviceTrees/blob/a7bd4fd23d56003146fcd426f52a7b627abcc512/src/arm/am335x-bone-common-univ.dtsi#L199-L200
2) Afterwards Also added the same pin mode in pinmux to show on `config-pin` side:
  https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleBoard-DeviceTrees/blob/a7bd4fd23d56003146fcd426f52a7b627abcc512/src/arm/am335x-bone-common-univ.dtsi#L1603-L1614
3) I have also added phandle for gpmc too in bone bus file:
  https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleBoard-DeviceTrees/blob/a7bd4fd23d56003146fcd426f52a7b627abcc512/src/arm/bbb-bone-buses.dtsi#L427-L430
4) Finally added the BeagleWire overlay too in `src/arn/overlays`:
    - [BW-ICE40Cape-00A0.dts](https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleBoard-DeviceTrees/blob/a7bd4fd23d56003146fcd426f52a7b627abcc512/src/arm/overlays/BW-ICE40Cape-00A0.dts)  
     - [BW-ICE40Cape-00A0_LKM.dts](https://github.com/BeagleWire/BeagleBoard-DeviceTrees/blob/a7bd4fd23d56003146fcd426f52a7b627abcc512/src/arm/overlays/BW-ICE40Cape-00A0_LKM.dts)  
     
 Demo of working video:
 https://asciinema.org/a/ICSlldHwYC4RtOHG0oJkIRUBd
 
regards,
Omkar Bhilare
ombhilare999@gmail.com

pr_body:
Added beaglewire platform and target file.
- Platform file for beaglewire can be found [here](https://github.com/litex-hub/litex-boards/blob/db9c98b28afcb64058662ff254f465cd63ff6a2a/litex_boards/platforms/beaglewire.py)
- Target file for beaglewire can be found [here](https://github.com/litex-hub/litex-boards/blob/db9c98b28afcb64058662ff254f465cd63ff6a2a/litex_boards/targets/beaglewire_crossover.py)
- Detailed guide for how to use the beaglewire litex can be found [here](https://beaglewire.github.io/Blogs/BeagleWire-Litex.html)

Demo of working litex on beaglewire with uart wb crossover: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mx4KWYq29I0

kindly review it and let me know if any changes are required. 

regards,
omkar bhilare
ombhilare999@gmail.com
